      <h1 class='title'>Honours System</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c53WS</cite>
      
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_53ws' title='Col. 53WS &mdash; HL Deb 22 February 2005 vol 669 c53WS' name='column_53ws' href='#column_53ws' rel='bookmark'>53WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0669P0-04854'>
        <a name='S5LV0669P0_20050222_LWS_5'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-valerie-amos' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050222_LWS_5' title='Link to this speech by Ms Valerie Amos' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-valerie-amos" title="Ms Valerie Amos">Baroness Amos</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0669P0-04854">My right honourable friend the Prime Minister has made the following Written Ministerial Statement.</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04855">The Government's decision on changes to the honours system are contained in the Command Paper Reform of the Honours System (Cm 6479) which has been published today. Copies are being placed in the Libraries of the House.</p>
        </blockquote>
